text: Horst aan de Maas is a municipality in the Dutch province of Limburg. In 2019, 42,291 people lived there. It was created on 1 January 2001 from the former municipalities of Broekhuizen, Grubbenvorst and Horst. In 2010, the former municipalities Sevenum and part of Meerlo-Wanssum joined the municipality.
